Lawmakers from the government coalition are confident they will get the votes they need, “and many more,” to approve the reform, said lawmaker Juan Ramiro Robledo Ruiz, head of the lower house constitution committee. His group must approve the reform before it goes to both houses of Congress in September.&nbsp;

